<body class="cs-report">
  <header class="cs-report__header">
    <a href="https://crewsignal.org/reports/mediation/trackers/horizon/" class="cs-report__back">
      &larr; Horizon / CWA-AFA Mediation
    </a>

    <p class="cs-report__eyebrow">Mediation &amp; Negotiation &middot; Weekly Report</p>

    <h1 class="cs-report__title">Horizon / CWA-AFA</h1>
    <p class="cs-report__meta">
      NMB Docket: A-14102 &middot; Mediator: Michael Kelliher
    </p>

    <p class="cs-report__subtitle">Week Ending 2026.03.06</p>
  </header>

  <section class="cs-report__section">
    <h2 class="cs-report__section-title">Status Summary</h2>

    <p class="cs-report__body">
      Week ending 2026.03.06 did not produce a new public bargaining-table recap,
      company filing, or regulator notice. The clearest negotiations-related public
      development was a March 3 CWA-AFA Horizon mobilization post inviting members
      to a March 9 contract event at PDX.
    </p>

    <p class="cs-report__body">
      For lineholders, that means public visibility rose through mobilization rather
      than through bargaining detail. There was still no same-week public tentative
      agreement signal, ratification calendar, or release-from-mediation posture.
      The visible change was pressure, not closure.
    </p>

    <div class="cs-report__callout">
      <ul class="cs-report__list">
        <li><strong>Mobilization signal:</strong> The March 9 PDX event shows contract pressure activity remains active.</li>
        <li><strong>Public-record gap:</strong> No same-week bargaining summary surfaced to explain where talks stand article by article.</li>
        <li><strong>What matters next:</strong> The next meaningful public shift still needs to come from a table update, company filing, or formal process change.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="cs-report__section">
    <h2 class="cs-report__section-title">CrewSignal Watch Points</h2>

    <p class="cs-report__body">
      This week is a good example of why CrewSignal separates mobilization from
      bargaining closure. Contract visibility events can show continued member
      engagement and bargaining pressure, but they do not by themselves establish
      that a deal is close or that mediation posture has changed.
    </p>

    <p class="cs-report__body">
      Horizon&rsquo;s public record therefore remained thin but not dormant. The campaign
      stayed visible, yet the public did not receive a same-week bargaining narrative
      strong enough to say whether the parties were narrowing issues or simply holding pressure.
    </p>

    <div class="cs-report__callout cs-report__callout--neutral">
      <ul class="cs-report__list">
        <li><strong>Mediation track:</strong> No new same-week public process change identified.</li>
        <li><strong>Contract track:</strong> Public pressure increased, but bargaining detail did not.</li>
        <li><strong>System-wide:</strong> The March 9 event is a meaningful mobilization marker, but not yet a closing marker.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>

